properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 14 at 2:43PM AKST until January 16 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a High Wind
Watch, which is in effect from late Wednesday night through
Thursday evening.

* WHAT...Northeast winds 15 to 30 mph with gusts up to 60 mph.

* WHERE...Downtown Juneau, Douglas, West Juneau, and Thane.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM AKST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Objects will be blown around in the wind. High
profile vehicles will be difficult to manage.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Wind chills will be around zero. Winds
should ease in the evening. Winds are expected to increase again
early Thursday morning through Thursday evening. Northeast winds
20 to 30 mph with gusts of 60 mph or greater will be possible.
properties.instruction:
Prepare for possible power outages.

A high wind watch means there is the potential for a hazardous
high wind event.
